main_body:
The Government of the Federal Republic of Germany is hereby authorized to grant aid of DM 4 028 million to the German coal industry for the 1990 calendar year. The total amount shall be made up of the following aid:
1. aid totalling DM 3 550 million to sales of coal and coke to the Community iron and steel industry;
2. aid totalling DM 152 million under a scheme for maintaining the underground labour force in deep mines (Bergmannspraemie);
3. aid totalling DM 20 million for special depreciation;
4. aid totalling DM 306 million to finance social benefit schemes in the coal industry, corresponding to the difference between actual and standard social charges.
